    {
      "id": "core-loop-proof-task-summary-task",
      "type": "task",
      "label": "Prove one Twilite loop that feels inevitable",
      "position": {
        "x": -425,
        "y": 1663.9166666666667
      },
      "width": 380,
      "height": 220,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "body": "Goal: Prove one Twilite loop that feels inevitable\nStatus: open\n\nTasks in scope:\n1. Choose and name the first undeniable loop\n2. Walk the loop end to end and log friction\n3. Fix the blockers that break trust in the loop\n4. Make the outcome visibly legible\n5. Package the loop as a repeatable demo\n6. Only after proof, decide what expands next\n\nOpen questions:\n1. Which exact loop is the strongest first proof?\n2. What is the single biggest source of demo friction today?",
        "status": "open",
        "owner": "Michael",
        "priority": "critical",
        "estimateHours": "3",
        "acceptanceCriteria": [
          "One candidate loop is chosen",
          "The loop has a clear start, action, and visible finish",
